Jeff Wicks, News24Police Search and Rescue members retrieve the body of the suspected burglar. (Jeff Wicks, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A suspected burglar plunged seven floors to his death while trying to evade capture in a high-rise flat complex in central Durban on Friday morning, KwaZulu-Natal police said.The occupant of a flat the thief broke into confronted him, Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said.He tried to get away by climbing through a window, lost his footing and fell. Police Search and Rescue Unit officers had to climb a terrace to recover his body.An inquest was opened at the Point police station. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.